canonical:
  title: 又謝不立行省書
  author: 崔瀣
  language: lzh
  text: 伏念小邦世荷累朝涵育國中君臣之分一皆依舊不料邇年樂旤之人閒起以致朝廷有議立省百姓聞之人不自安近者欽蒙聖旨一切禁之擧國上下實獲再生唯知蹈舞而已玆遣小介奉表進謝伏望善爲聞奏永示字小之仁不勝忻慶不宣
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 又謝不立行省書
  author: 崔瀣
  language: lzh
  text: 伏念小邦。世荷累朝涵育。國中君臣之分。一皆依舊。不料邇年樂旤之人。閒起以致朝廷有議立省。百姓聞之。人不自安。近者欽蒙聖旨。一切禁之。擧國上下。實獲再生。唯知蹈舞而已。玆遣小介。奉表進謝。伏望善爲聞奏。永示字小之仁。不勝忻慶。不宣。
korean:
  title: 우사 부립행성 서
  author: 최해
  language: kor
  text: 엎드려 생각건대, 저의 나라는 대대로 역대 조정의 함육(涵育)을 받아 나라 안에 군신의 분별이 모두 옛날과 같습니다. 뜻밖에 근년에 재앙을 즐기는 사람이 중간에 일어나 조정에서 행중서성(行中書省)을 두자는 의논이 있기에 이르렀으므로 백성들은 그 말을 듣고 사람마다 마음이 아주 편안치 않았었는데, 요즘에 일체를 금지한다는 성상의 교지를 받잡고 온 나라의 윗사람이나 아랫사람이 참으로 다시 살아남을 얻어 오직 춤출 뿐입니다. 이에 사신을 보내어 표문을 받들고 사례하오니, 엎드려 바라건대 잘 들으시고 작고 연약한 백성을 사랑하고 애처롭게 여기는 어진 마음을 길이 보이소서. 기쁘고 경사스러움을 이기지 못하여 다 말씀드리지 못하옵니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0650_010_0080&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Another Memorial of Gratitude for the Non-Establishment of a Provincial Administration
  author: Choe Hae
  language: eng
  text: I humbly reflect that our small realm has generation upon generation received the nurturing care of successive imperial courts. Within our nation, the distinction between ruler and subject remains as it has always been. Yet unexpectedly, in recent years, those who would profit from calamity stirred unrest, leading the imperial court to consider establishing a provincial administration here. When the common people heard this, not a soul found peace. But now, having received your sacred edict forbidding this measure entirely, all the realm—from highest to lowest—has truly been given new life. Our people can do nothing but dance with joy. Thus I send this humble emissary bearing this memorial of gratitude. I humbly beseech you to present this favorably to the throne, that you might eternally display your benevolent heart toward our small and weak people. Our joy and gratitude know no bounds, and these words cannot express it all.
  footnotes:
    - This memorial responds to the court's decision to rescind plans to establish a provincial administration (行中書省) in the author's native realm, likely referring to Goryeo or one of its territories during the Yuan Dynasty's period of influence.
    - The reference to 'those who profit from calamity' suggests court factions or officials who sought to extend centralized control, viewed as a threat to local autonomy.
